==English==

===Etymology===
From French ''[[détour]]'', from ''[[détourner]]'' ‘turn away’.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˈdi:tʊə/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A [[diversion]] or [[deviation]] from one's original route.

===Verb===
{{en-verb}}

# {{intransitive}} To make a detour.
# {{transitive}} To direct or send on a detour.